{"Mode":{"InScheme":{"Id":"http://data.europa.eu/snb/learning-assessment/25831c2","Type":"ConceptScheme"},"PrefLabel":{"En":"Online"},"Id":"http://data.europa.eu/snb/learning-assessment/920fbb3cbe","Type":"Concept"},"DcType":null,"Title":{"En":"Intercultural Communication in an English-speaking World"},"AdmissionsProcedure":null,"ApplicationDeadline":"2024-08-18","Description":{"En":"**The module is divided into two parts:**\n\nThe first module, Perspectives on International Communication (2.5 ECTS), focuses on intercultural communication in general, and takes as its point of departure some central theories, notions and practices from anthropology and sociology, in order to provide a framework for a critical analysis and understanding of obstacles and pitfalls in intercultural communication. The aim of the course module is to provide the students with tools to be able to identify and remedy communication breakdowns in favour of creating less friction in professional intercultural contexts.\n\nThe second part,\u00A0Intercultural Communication with English as a Lingua Franca (5ECTS), builds on the theories and notions studied in the first part, but here, the focus is on communicative situations where English is the language of communication. Here, linguistic features will also be analysed and discussed as possible obstacles and/or resources to successful communication."},"LearningAchievementSpecification":{"EQFLevel":{"InScheme":{"Id":"http://data.europa.eu/snb/eqf/25831c2","Type":"ConceptScheme"},"PrefLabel":{"En":"Level 6"},"Id":"http://data.europa.eu/snb/eqf/6","Type":"Concept"},"CreditPoint":{"Framework":{"InScheme":{"Id":"http://data.europa.eu/snb/education-credit/25831c2","Type":"ConceptScheme"},"PrefLabel":{"En":"European Credit Transfer System"},"Id":"http://data.europa.eu/snb/education-credit/6fcec5c5af","Type":"Concept"},"Point":"7,5","Id":"urn:epass:creditPoint:ffb873e1-c803-ef11-9f89-0022487fecad","Type":"CreditPoint"},"LearningOutcome":[{"Title":{"En":"Comparison"},"RelatedESCOSkill":[{"Notation":"Skill","InScheme":{"Id":"http://data.europa.eu/esco/concept-scheme/skills","Type":"ConceptScheme"},"PrefLabel":{"En":"demonstrate consideration"},"Id":"http://data.europa.eu/esco/skill/9d75743b-317a-4bc4-b93f-c72e3ceba377","Type":"Concept"},{"Notation":"Skill","InScheme":{"Id":"http://data.europa.eu/esco/concept-scheme/skills","Type":"ConceptScheme"},"PrefLabel":{"En":"demonstrate intercultural competence"},"Id":"http://data.europa.eu/esco/skill/c10d5d87-36cf-42f5-8a12-e560fb5f4af8","Type":"Concept"}],"AdditionalNote":{"NoteLiteral":{"En":"Be able to compare and contrast Swedish culture to other cultures in the world where English is/may be spoken in a professional context."},"Id":"urn:eciu:note:3a3ccbe4-c803-ef11-9f89-000d3a398ca7","Type":"Note"},"Id":"urn:epass:learningOutcome:ffb873e1-c803-ef11-9f89-0022487fecad-1","Type":"LearningOutcome"},{"Title":{"En":"Theoretical knowledge"},"RelatedESCOSkill":[{"Notation":"Skill","InScheme":{"Id":"http://data.europa.eu/esco/concept-scheme/skills","Type":"ConceptScheme"},"PrefLabel":{"En":"demonstrate intercultural competence"},"Id":"http://data.europa.eu/esco/skill/c10d5d87-36cf-42f5-8a12-e560fb5f4af8","Type":"Concept"}],"AdditionalNote":{"NoteLiteral":{"En":"Identify basic academic concepts relevant to intercultural awareness."},"Id":"urn:eciu:note:11cbc7f0-c803-ef11-9f89-000d3a398ca7","Type":"Note"},"Id":"urn:epass:learningOutcome:ffb873e1-c803-ef11-9f89-0022487fecad-2","Type":"LearningOutcome"},{"Title":{"En":"Intercultural awareness"},"RelatedESCOSkill":[{"Notation":"Skill","InScheme":{"Id":"http://data.europa.eu/esco/concept-scheme/skills","Type":"ConceptScheme"},"PrefLabel":{"En":"listening and asking questions"},"Id":"http://data.europa.eu/esco/skill/S1.7.3","Type":"Concept"},{"Notation":"Skill","InScheme":{"Id":"http://data.europa.eu/esco/concept-scheme/skills","Type":"ConceptScheme"},"PrefLabel":{"En":"solving problems"},"Id":"http://data.europa.eu/esco/skill/S1.9","Type":"Concept"}],"AdditionalNote":{"NoteLiteral":{"En":"Critically discuss basic academic concepts relevant to intercultural awareness."},"Id":"urn:eciu:note:73cbc7f0-c803-ef11-9f89-000d3a398ca7","Type":"Note"},"Id":"urn:epass:learningOutcome:ffb873e1-c803-ef11-9f89-0022487fecad-3","Type":"LearningOutcome"},{"Title":{"En":"Application of theory"},"RelatedESCOSkill":[{"Notation":"Skill","InScheme":{"Id":"http://data.europa.eu/esco/concept-scheme/skills","Type":"ConceptScheme"},"PrefLabel":{"En":"demonstrate willingness to learn"},"Id":"http://data.europa.eu/esco/skill/A1.8.0","Type":"Concept"}],"AdditionalNote":{"NoteLiteral":{"En":"Apply basic sociological and anthropological theories and concepts in international contexts where English is the language of communication."},"Id":"urn:eciu:note:59c4a1e5-c803-ef11-9f89-0022488b0cca","Type":"Note"},"Id":"urn:epass:learningOutcome:ffb873e1-c803-ef11-9f89-0022487fecad-4","Type":"LearningOutcome"},{"Title":{"En":"Presentation and language skills"},"RelatedESCOSkill":[{"Notation":"Skill","InScheme":{"Id":"http://data.europa.eu/esco/concept-scheme/skills","Type":"ConceptScheme"},"PrefLabel":{"En":"English"},"Id":"http://data.europa.eu/esco/skill/6d3edede-8951-4621-a835-e04323300fa0","Type":"Concept"}],"AdditionalNote":{"NoteLiteral":{"En":"Give an oral presentation of an analysis of an intercultural case study, using English appropriate for professional settings."},"Id":"urn:eciu:note:af96afeb-c803-ef11-9f89-0022488b0cca","Type":"Note"},"Id":"urn:epass:learningOutcome:ffb873e1-c803-ef11-9f89-0022487fecad-5","Type":"LearningOutcome"},{"Title":{"En":"Communication"},"RelatedESCOSkill":[{"Notation":"Skill","InScheme":{"Id":"http://data.europa.eu/esco/concept-scheme/skills","Type":"ConceptScheme"},"PrefLabel":{"En":"English"},"Id":"http://data.europa.eu/esco/skill/6d3edede-8951-4621-a835-e04323300fa0","Type":"Concept"},{"Notation":"Skill","InScheme":{"Id":"http://data.europa.eu/esco/concept-scheme/skills","Type":"ConceptScheme"},"PrefLabel":{"En":"work in teams"},"Id":"http://data.europa.eu/esco/skill/60c78287-22eb-4103-9c8c-28deaa460da0","Type":"Concept"}],"AdditionalNote":{"NoteLiteral":{"En":"Successfully communicate in English in a professional and international environment."},"Id":"urn:eciu:note:ee96afeb-c803-ef11-9f89-0022488b0cca","Type":"Note"},"Id":"urn:epass:learningOutcome:ffb873e1-c803-ef11-9f89-0022487fecad-6","Type":"LearningOutcome"}],"LearningSetting":null,"Mode":null,"Title":{"En":"Intercultural Communication in an English-speaking World"},"DcType":null,"HomePage":null,"VolumeOfLearning":null,"Id":"urn:eciu:qualification:ffb873e1-c803-ef11-9f89-0022487fecad","Type":"Qualification"},"IsPartOf":{"Mode":null,"DcType":null,"Title":{"En":"Intercultural Communication in an English-speaking World"},"AdmissionsProcedure":null,"ApplicationDeadline":null,"Description":null,"LearningAchievementSpecification":null,"IsPartOf":null,"Temporal":null,"ProvidedBy":null,"LearningActivitySpecification":null,"BannerImage":null,"MoreInformation":null,"Id":"urn:eciu:learningOpportunity:3e769a56-fbef-ed11-8849-6045bd886566","Type":"LearningOpportunity"},"Temporal":{"EndDate":"2024-08-26T00:00:00Z","Name":{"En":"Temporal"},"StartDate":"2025-01-19T00:00:00Z"},"ProvidedBy":{"Location":null,"Logo":null,"LegalName":{"En":"LINKOPINGS UNIVERSITET (LIU)"},"Registration":null,"Homepage":null,"Id":"urn:eciu:org:f1122d1d-6a54-ed11-bba2-6045bd886566","Type":"Organisation"},"LearningActivitySpecification":{"Mode":null,"DcType":null,"Title":{"En":""},"Description":null,"MoreInformation":[{"NoteLiteral":"The expected workload of the micro-module is around 8 hours per week. This includes not only the the scheduled activities, such as lectures, seminars and workshops, but also individual time invested in group work, self-study, seminar preparation, assignment writing etc.\n\n**Teaching and working methods**\n\nThe course encompasses lectures and seminars. Students are to study the course material and prepare for group discussions and mini-presentations in the seminars. Feedback on language, content and delivery is provided by teachers and peers. The language of instruction and examination is English. In addition, the student is expected to study on their own.\n\n**Examination**\n\nActive Seminar Attendance 1 - 1ECTS\n\nOral Presentation on Case Studies 1 - 1.5 ECTS\n\nActive Seminar Attendance 2 - 2 ECTS\n\nOral Presentation on Case Studies 2 - 3ECTS\n\nFor the syllabus of the module please see [here](https://studieinfo.liu.se/en/kurs/701G23/ht-2024#syllabus).","Subject":{"InScheme":{"Id":"urn:eciu:note","Type":"ConceptScheme"},"PrefLabel":{"En":"ParticipantInformation"},"Id":"ffb873e1-c803-ef11-9f89-0022487fecad","Type":"Concept"}}],"HasPart":null,"Id":"urn:eciu:learningActivitySpec:ffb873e1-c803-ef11-9f89-0022487fecad","Type":"LearningActivitySpecification"},"BannerImage":null,"MoreInformation":[{"NoteLiteral":"","Subject":{"InScheme":{"Id":"urn:eciu:note","Type":"ConceptScheme"},"PrefLabel":{"En":"SourceIdentifier"},"Id":"ffb873e1-c803-ef11-9f89-0022487fecad","Type":"Concept"}},{"NoteLiteral":"Learn to successfully communicate in English in a professional and international environment","Subject":{"InScheme":{"Id":"urn:eciu:note","Type":"ConceptScheme"},"PrefLabel":{"En":"SubTitle"},"Id":"ffb873e1-c803-ef11-9f89-0022487fecad","Type":"Concept"}},{"NoteLiteral":"This course is suited for anyone interested in improving their professional communication with people from other cultures as well as other countries where English is the language of communication.","Subject":{"InScheme":{"Id":"urn:eciu:note","Type":"ConceptScheme"},"PrefLabel":{"En":"Introduction"},"Id":"ffb873e1-c803-ef11-9f89-0022487fecad","Type":"Concept"}},{"NoteLiteral":"True","Subject":{"InScheme":{"Id":"urn:eciu:note","Type":"ConceptScheme"},"PrefLabel":{"En":"GenerateMicroCredentials"},"Id":"ffb873e1-c803-ef11-9f89-0022487fecad","Type":"Concept"}},{"NoteLiteral":"**Deadline for applications**: Sunday, 18 August 2024\n\n**Entry Requirements**:\n\n- The student must be admitted to studies on the university Level.\n\n- English level B2 (CEFR)\n\nAll applicants are required to submit a transcript of records and a proof of English (e.g. internationally recognised test, university courses, certificate from home university).\n\nYou will receive a results notification within 5 days from the application deadline. If you are admitted, you will be contacted by the host university regarding the next steps in the process.","Subject":{"InScheme":{"Id":"urn:eciu:note","Type":"ConceptScheme"},"PrefLabel":{"En":"AdmissionProcessInformation"},"Id":"ffb873e1-c803-ef11-9f89-0022487fecad","Type":"Concept"}},{"NoteLiteral":"False","Subject":{"InScheme":{"Id":"urn:eciu:note","Type":"ConceptScheme"},"PrefLabel":{"En":"SimplifiedAdmissionProcess"},"Id":"ffb873e1-c803-ef11-9f89-0022487fecad","Type":"Concept"}},{"NoteLiteral":"2024-06-15","Subject":{"InScheme":{"Id":"urn:eciu:note","Type":"ConceptScheme"},"PrefLabel":{"En":"ApplicationPeriodStartDate"},"Id":"ffb873e1-c803-ef11-9f89-0022487fecad","Type":"Concept"}},{"NoteLiteral":"10","Subject":{"InScheme":{"Id":"urn:eciu:note","Type":"ConceptScheme"},"PrefLabel":{"En":"MaximumNumberOfSeats"},"Id":"ffb873e1-c803-ef11-9f89-0022487fecad","Type":"Concept"}},{"NoteLiteral":"False","Subject":{"InScheme":{"Id":"urn:eciu:note","Type":"ConceptScheme"},"PrefLabel":{"En":"ECIULMSENabled"},"Id":"ffb873e1-c803-ef11-9f89-0022487fecad","Type":"Concept"}},{"NoteLiteral":"","Subject":{"InScheme":{"Id":"urn:eciu:note","Type":"ConceptScheme"},"PrefLabel":{"En":"LMSUrl"},"Id":"ffb873e1-c803-ef11-9f89-0022487fecad","Type":"Concept"}},{"NoteLiteral":"","Subject":{"InScheme":{"Id":"urn:eciu:note","Type":"ConceptScheme"},"PrefLabel":{"En":"TeamAccessDate"},"Id":"ffb873e1-c803-ef11-9f89-0022487fecad","Type":"Concept"}},{"NoteLiteral":"false","Subject":{"InScheme":{"Id":"urn:eciu:note","Type":"ConceptScheme"},"PrefLabel":{"En":"SelfPaced"},"Id":"ffb873e1-c803-ef11-9f89-002248